"title": "7751: persuasion",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7751: persuasion",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Attempting to win others over to one's own point of view. It can be either positive, as with preaching the gospel, or it can spring from a malign intent to seduce people from the truth.</p>\n<h2>Means of persuasion</h2>\n<h3>The persuasiveness of argument</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:15\">ACT 16:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:3\">JDG 19:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:7\">JDG 19:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:35\">2SA 3:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:40\">ACT 5:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:32-Acts19:41\">ACT 19:32–19:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:14\">ACT 21:14</a></p>\n<h3>The persuasiveness of proof</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:3\">ACT 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:25-Gen45:28\">GEN 45:25–45:28</a></p>\n<h3>The persuasiveness of experience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:24-1Cor14:25\">1CO 14:24–14:25</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The first Christians were persuaded of the truth of their faith</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:12\">2TI 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:20-Rom4:21\">ROM 4:20–4:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:38-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:38–8:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:14\">2TI 3:14</a></p>\n<h2>The apostles tried to persuade others of the truth of the gospel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:4\">ACT 18:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:2-Acts17:4\">ACT 17:2–17:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:8\">ACT 19:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:26-Acts26:29\">ACT 26:26–26:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:23-Acts28:24\">ACT 28:23–28:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:11\">2CO 5:11</a></p>\n<h2>Scripture advises patience when seeking to persuade those in power</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:15\">PRO 25:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:1-Luke18:5\">LUK 18:1–18:5</a></p>\n<h2>Scripture warns against the persuasiveness of evil</h2>\n<h3>The persuasiveness of adulterers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:21\">PRO 7:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:3\">PRO 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:5\">PRO 7:5</a></p>\n<h3>The persuasiveness of false prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:15\">JER 28:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Examples of God's servants suffering through the persuasiveness of others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:20\">MAT 27:20</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:11\">MRK 15:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:19\">ACT 14:19</a></p>",
